<I=C>
PathItem.strokeMiterLimit 

  app.activeDocument.pathItems[index].strokeMiterLimit  

Description

When a default stroke join is set to mitered, this property specifies when the join will be converted to
beveled (squared-off ) by default. The default miter limit of 4 means that when the length of the point
reaches four times the stroke weight, the join switches from a miter join to a bevel join. A value of 1
specifies a bevel join. Range: 1 to 500. Default: 4

Type

Number (double)

