<I=r>
TracingObject 

  TracingObject  

Description

A tracing object, which associates source raster art item with a vector-art plug-in group created by
tracing. Scripts can initiate tracing using <L=1u#2c> PlacedItem.trace </L> or
<L=1N#2y> RasterItem.trace() </L> .

The resulting PluginItem object represents the vector art group, and has this object in its tracing
property.

A script can force the tracing operation by calling <L=9#2X> Application.redraw() </L> . The operation is
asynchronous, so a script should call   redraw   after creating the tracing object, but before accessing
its properties or expanding the tracing to convert it to an art item group.

The read-only properties that describe the tracing result have valid values only after the first tracing
operation completes. A value of 0 indicates that the operation has not yet been completed.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Properties 

